Frank Lackteen https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frank_Lackteen 0 Frank Lackteen (August 29, 1897 – July 8, 1968) was a Lebanese-born American film actor best known for his antagonistic roles. He appeared in nearly 200 films between 1916 and 1965, including several Three Stooges shorts. Lacteen was born in Kab-Elias, Lebanon, and attended an American school in Lebanon.Lacteen made his first American film in 1916 and was often seen as a villain in silent films. Many of his film appearances came in Westerns and serials.Lackteen died from a respiratory failure on July 8, 1968 in Woodland Hills, Los Angeles.
